      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BAD AND BERTHA (8) has proven too strong with wins at her last two, scoring by 7 lengths (34.49) last time and by 4.5 lengths (27.56) two back. Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and a minor placing from four starts. Can continue on with her winning form. EXTREME TENSION (1) turned in a plain run last time when eighth at Grafton over 450m behind Badger's Beast (26.09) in a NG. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. In the mix. FEDERAL BLONDE (2) dropped out early but hit the line hard and charged to a strong half a length win (30.39) at this track in P5. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Can go close again if runs up to latest figure. POWER OF WHISKEY (7) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.",
